Sullivans Nicolaides Pathology

Sullivan Nicolaides Pathology is one of the largest members of the Sonic Healthcare group. Sonic Healthcare is an independent, Australian owned, publicly listed company, operating in the specialities of pathology and radiology.

All Sonic practices are medically managed and are thus well placed to appreciate the special needs of doctors and their patients. SNP is a well-respected, established pathology practice, offering comprehensive, high quality pathology services for doctors, private hospitals and nursing homes in Queensland northern New South Wales and Darwin. We are medically managed by pathologists and a select and highly qualified team of scientific and senior management staff.

SNP was formed in 1956 when Drs John Sullivan and Nick Nicolaides started a small pathology practice to service local families in and around Brisbane. Since then it has grown to one of the largest pathology practices in Australia.

Our practice is managed by doctors for doctors. Our CEO, Dr Michael Harrison, is a pathologist. All department directors are pathologists, and pathologists are represented at all levels of management.

Our pathologists and senior management staff encourage doctors to contact them for information, consultation, or advice at any time. Our  Territory Managers are available to assist clinicians and their staff with the practicalities of using our services.
